London Stock Exchange Halts Trading System Amid ‘System Issues’

-- B y   A n d r e w   R u m m e r
-- 
2011-02-25T08:14:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/london-stock-exchange-halts-sets-trading-in-shares-citing-system-issues-.html
  London Stock Exchange Group Plc 
halted its SETS and SETSqx trading systems and said  “no
continuous trading is currently taking place in order driven
securities.” The company made the announcement on its website.  Earlier, the exchange said it was investigating “potential
system issues.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  